{
  "texts": [
    "In comparison to traditional supervised contrastive learning, MSS-Cl introduces additional adversarial iterations between trigger words of the same class and those of different classes within a single episode.",
    "This strengthens the model's ability to pull together trigger words of the same category in the feature representation space while simultaneously pushing apart clusters of samples from different categories.",
    "As described in Sect. 4.2.1, within different channels of token representations, some may contain a generic representation describing the event type, while others may capture the specificity of trigger words.",
    "Assuming h 1 1 and h 1 2 contain generic representations of different trigger words from the same event type, and h 2 1 and h 2 2 capture the specificity of different trigger words from the same event type, MSS-Cl not only possesses the capability to bring together the generic representations of different trigger words from the same category but also learns the similarity between the specific representations of different trigger words from the same category.",
    "This significantly contributes to enhancing the model's generalization.In addition, we add the prototype-query contrastive loss (pqcl) proposed by [48] to MPC-CA, and the formula is listed as follows:L pqcl = i∈{x i,y i }=Q -L pqcl i (20) L pqcl i = log exp hi • p c=y i /τ c ∈C exp hi • p c /τ(21)The blue arrows in Fig. 3 represents this process."
  ]
}